<TEXT>
A US Coast Guard cutter escorted a Soviet 
research vessel into Hilo Harbor so a crew member could be treated 
for an eye ailment a Coast Guard spokesman said today 
The 150foot Fedor Matisen which tied up Friday night at Hawaii 
Island also was allowed to take on water during the medical 
stopover Christopher Kimbrough said 
A paramedic from the Hawaii County Fire Department was ferried 
to the Fedor Matisen aboard the cutter Cape Cross earlier Friday to 
verify the mans ailment Bob Schenck another Coast Guard 
spokesman said Friday night The ailment prevented the man from 
looking into bright light Schenck said 
The Soviet vessel was scheduled to leave Hilo today Kimbrough 
said 
